-- Nigeria Eases Past Tahiti 6-1 in Confederations Cup Soccer Match
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-06-17T22:43:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-17/nigeria-eases-past-tahiti-6-1-in-confederations-cup-soccer-match.html
Nnamdi Oduamadi scored three goals
and Uwa Echiejile added two more as Nigeria routed tournament
newcomer Tahiti 6-1 in soccer’s  Confederations Cup .  The first meeting between the countries completed the
opening round of group-stage games at the warm-up for next
year’s World Cup in  Brazil .  Echiejile opened the scoring for Nigeria after five minutes
at Estadio Mineirao in Belo Horizonte, Brazil, and Oduamadi
added two first-half goals for the African champion.  Jonathan Tehau got Oceania champion Tahiti’s first goal at
a senior FIFA tournament after 54 minutes before scoring against
his own team 15 minutes later.  Man of the match Oduamadi notched his third goal after 76
minutes and Echiejile made it 6-1 four minutes later.  Brazil faces Mexico in the next game, on June 19 in
Fortaleza, when Italy also takes on  Japan  in Recife.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dex McLuskey in Dallas at 
